<br>
EverQuest:<br>
$54.99(*2) = $109.98 (not including sales tax)<br>
<br>
Ruins of Kunark Expansion:<br>
$29.99(*2) = $59.98 (not including sales tax)<br>
<br>
Scars of Velious Expansion:<br>
$29.99(*2) = $59.98 (not including sales tax)<br>
<br>
Shadows of Luclin Expansion:<br>
$29.99(*2) = $59.98 (not including sales tax)<br>
---------------<br>
Total = $289.92<br>
---------------<br>
Two people for (1) year of monthly subscriptions:<br>
($9.89(*2) *(12 mon.)) = $237.36 (not including credit card charges)<br>
Two people for (3) years of already paid monthly subscriptions:<br>
($9.89(*2) *(36 mon.)) = $712.08 (not including credit card charges)<br>
---------------<br>
Two people per (1) year monthly subscriptions, with new price:<br>
($12.95(*2) *(12 mon.)) = $310.80 (not including credit card charges)<br>
Two people for (3) more years of EQ:<br>
($12.95(*2) *(36 mon.)) = $932.40 (not including credit card charges)<br>
---------------<br>
Total = $1,002.00 (software purchase w/ old price plan).<br>
Total = $1,222.32 (software purchase w/ new price plan).<br>
---------------<br>
Monthly ISP charges for broadband (shared access) per year:<br>
$49.99(*12) mon. = $599.88<br>
Monthly ISP charges for broadband (shared access) for (3) years:<br>
$49.99(*36) mon. = $1,799.64<br>
*note* I got broadband mainly because of EverQuest, not because I really needed it, since EverQuest &quot;requires&quot; internet access, I'm factoring my ISP in.<br>
--------------<br>
For the previous (3) years of EverQuest and Broadband access:<br>
Total = $2,801.64 <br>
--------------<br>
For the next (3) years of EverQuest and Broadband access (not including additional expansions):<br>
Total = $3,021.96<br>
--------------<br>
Old price plan (for the past (3) years, for (1) game with (3) expansions): <br>
$77.82 per month <br>
--------------<br>
New price plan (for the next (3) years, for (1) game with (3) expansions, not including future expansions): <br>
$83.94 per month <br>
--------------<br>
<br>
*note* Prices are based on a &quot;month-to-month&quot; payment plan, and doesn't take into account sales taxes, credit card charges &quot;where applicable&quot;, changes in ISP charges, or hardware upgrades, or even people paying $50.00 to move a character to another account, where they had to purchase the game, along with it's expansions again. These prices may vary for people, it's just based on what I know I've paid, not anyone else.<br>
<br>
Always include what you've already paid, such as buying the game and it's expansions, so based on the previous years, using the &quot;a movie is still more expensive&quot; concept, that would imply that I'd be willing to pay $77.82 per month, so that two people could see the same (4) movies, for (3) consecutive years in a row, where I am required to work, and devote many hours to see more of what is essentially; variations of the same thing. <br>
<br>
Broken down to $2.56 per day for the past (3) years, I could have rented (1) new release movie per day, everyday for the past (3) years. Personally I don't mind the price &quot;adjustment&quot;, but I do think there may be a lot of upset people over it.<br>
